  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Alone, our secondary analyses of experimental data contribute to a large set of observations on how coding properties vary with theta phase in the hippocampus.",
    "Of note is phase precession, in which different phases preferentially encode different segments within a firing field as it is traversed, with later phases tuned to earlier segments 67.",
    "Phase precession is most widely reported for place cells and traversals of physical space, but it also appears during the experience of other sequences, such as images and tasks [68] [69] [70].",
    "Our analysis implies that the sharpness of tuning is not constant throughout traversals.",
    "In particular, CA3 neurons are more sharply tuned at early positions in place fields, while CA1 neurons are more sharply tuned at late positions (Supplementary Fig. 5I, J)."
  ],
